## guide:// URI Scheme

This project exposes content via the `guide://` URI scheme, listed in MCP `resources/templates/list`.

### Content URIs
- `guide://expression` — retrieve content by expression, such as a category name, collection name, or combined expression like `docs,tasks`
- `guide://expression/pattern` — retrieve content filtered by glob pattern

### Command URIs
- `guide://_command` — execute a server command
- `guide://_command/args` — command with positional arguments, for example `guide://_perm/write/add/docs/`
- `guide://_command/args?key=value` — command with keyword arguments

### Resolution
- Prefer MCP resource discovery and direct resource reads when the client supports them.
- Use the `read_resource` tool as a fallback for clients that only expose tools.
